  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400\u0012F (200\u0012C).",
    "Season the lamb with salt, pepper, and oregano.",
    "In a small saucepan, combine the reduced red wine, honey, and lemon juice.",
    "Bring the sauce to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened.",
    "Place the lamb in a roasting pan and spoon the sauce over the top.",
    "Roast the lamb in the preheated oven for 20 minutes per pound, or until it reaches an internal temperature of 145\u0012F (63\u0012C).",
    "While the lamb is cooking, poach the eggs in a separate saucepan of simmering water.",
    "To serve, slice the lamb and top with a dollop of red wine jelly and a poached egg.",
    "Garnish with chopped fresh parsley and serve immediately."
  ],
